By: Zhuangzi
Locus:
  Chapter: 16
  Paragraph: 2
Title: Mending The Inborn Nature
---
The men of ancient times who practiced the Way employed tranquility to
cultivate knowledge. Knowledge lived in them, yet they did nothing for
its sake. So they may be said to have employed knowledge to cultivate
tranquility. Knowledge and tranquility took turns cultivating each
other, and harmony and order emerged from the inborn nature.
